{%- comment -%}
  feature-flags.liquid — runtime feature toggles for HairMNL theme.

  Usage in any template:
    {%- include 'feature-flags' -%}
    {%- if feature_new_cart_drawer -%}
      ... new variant ...
    {%- else -%}
      ... existing ...
    {%- endif -%}

  Each flag is evaluated at server render time so it works with
  Liquid conditionals (no JS needed). Override sources, in priority
  order:
    1. URL param `?_ff_FLAG_NAME=true|false` (admin/QA only — checked
       via request.host containing 'myshopify.com' to keep this off
       production-customer-facing logic)
    2. Customer tag `feature:FLAG_NAME` on the logged-in customer
    3. Cart attribute `feature:FLAG_NAME` (set via cart.attributes)
    4. Hardcoded default below

  When flipping a flag from false → true:
    - Test on draft theme first
    - Roll out to beta-tester customer tag, monitor RUM/error rates
    - Then default to true for everyone, remove the flag entirely
      after 1-2 release cycles when confident

  When adding a new flag:
    1. Default it to FALSE
    2. Add the {% if feature_X %} branches in template code
    3. Test by adding URL param `?_ff_X=true` on draft
    4. Once verified, you can flip the default OR roll out via tags

  Cost: ~200 bytes per page render of Liquid execution. No JS, no CSS,
  no network requests. Pure server-side branching.
{%- endcomment -%}

{%- liquid
  # ============================================================
  # FLAG DEFAULTS — keep this list small (< 5 active at any time)
  # ============================================================
  # No active feature flags currently. Add to this list as needed.
  # Example (kept commented for the next person):
  #   assign feature_new_cart_drawer = false
  #   assign feature_static_judgeme = true
  #   assign feature_unified_product_card = false

  # ============================================================
  # OVERRIDE LOGIC (applies to every flag defined above)
  # ============================================================
  # Customer tag override: if logged-in customer has tag
  # `feature:FLAG_NAME`, that flag is forced true.
  # E.g. tag a customer as `feature:new_cart_drawer` to give them
  # the new cart drawer regardless of the default.
  if customer
    for tag in customer.tags
      if tag contains 'feature:'
        assign flag_var_name = tag | replace: 'feature:', 'feature_'
        # Note: Liquid can't dynamically assign vars by string name in
        # standard Shopify Liquid. To activate per-customer flags, add
        # explicit `assign feature_X = true` blocks per tag here.
      endif
    endfor
  endif

  # Cart attribute override: if cart.attributes['feature:FLAG_NAME']
  # is 'true', the flag is enabled. Useful for cart-scoped experiments.
  # (Same dynamic-assign limitation as above — explicit branches needed
  # per cart attribute that should map to a flag.)

  # URL override (DRAFT/STAGING ONLY — never customer-visible on .com)
  # Activated when the request hostname contains 'myshopify.com'
  # (i.e. preview / draft URL, not the production custom domain).
  # Each flag's URL override is `?_ff_FLAG_NAME=true|false`.
  # Implement explicit branches when you want URL override on a flag:
  #   if request.host contains 'myshopify.com'
  #     if request.url contains '_ff_new_cart_drawer=true'
  #       assign feature_new_cart_drawer = true
  #     elsif request.url contains '_ff_new_cart_drawer=false'
  #       assign feature_new_cart_drawer = false
  #     endif
  #   endif
-%}
